text: trans-Propenylbenzene is an organic compound with the formula C6H5CH=CHCH3. It is one of two isomers of 1-propenylbenzene. Both isomers are colorless flammable liquids. It is formed by the isomerization of allylbenzene. ==References== Category:Alkene derivatives Category:Aromatic hydrocarbons
title: Trans-Propenylbenzene
